00:09:26,064 --> 00:09:28,745
Tatarn's Facebook is public.

60
00:09:29,385 --> 00:09:32,625
It seems like he wants
to send someone a message.

61
00:09:33,345 --> 00:09:34,705
That someone

62
00:09:35,424 --> 00:09:36,665
could be Nut.

63
00:09:37,465 --> 00:09:39,465
But there's not
a single photo of Nut here.

64
00:09:40,465 --> 00:09:44,025
There's also no information
about Tatarn's whereabouts, job,

65
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,184
nor how to contact him.

66
00:09:55,145 --> 00:10:00,105
TATARN, OUR LIFE

67
00:10:07,225 --> 00:10:09,304
That man seems familiar.

68
00:10:11,785 --> 00:10:13,505
Is it someone who knows Nut?

69
00:10:16,745 --> 00:10:18,465
He's not just someone he knows.

70
00:10:19,145 --> 00:10:20,745
He's someone Nut loved.

71
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:30,985
Why would you look at his pictures?

72
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:34,265
Don't worry about it.

73
00:10:34,345 --> 00:10:36,025
He's the past.

74
00:10:36,105 --> 00:10:38,385
Now, you're the only one for Nut, okay?

75
00:11:01,944 --> 00:11:03,944
Are you and Nut in love?

76
00:11:05,304 --> 00:11:06,505
Yes.

77
00:11:09,665 --> 00:11:10,665
You got it right.

78
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:12,824
We are in love.

79
00:11:14,705 --> 00:11:16,544
Tofu makes me happy.

80
00:11:18,465 --> 00:11:20,544
He's the reason I can tolerate this house.

81
00:11:22,665 --> 00:11:25,785
What are you trying to do
by asking him behind my back?

82
00:11:27,585 --> 00:11:29,145
Are you driving him away again?

83
00:11:29,705 --> 00:11:31,385
Are you doing the same thing again?

84
00:11:38,505 --> 00:11:39,505
Don't go anywhere,

85
00:11:39,985 --> 00:11:41,705
or I'll go with you.

86
00:11:42,665 --> 00:11:45,705
If you can't accept it,
then I won't stay here.

87
00:11:46,905 --> 00:11:48,145
Where are you going?

88
00:11:49,824 --> 00:11:51,385
You're my son.

89
00:11:52,265 --> 00:11:53,944
Your son is gay!

90
00:11:55,824 --> 00:11:59,064
If you dream of a happy family
like you find in books,

91
00:11:59,865 --> 00:12:01,145
I can tell you now

92
00:12:01,785 --> 00:12:03,665
that it will never come true

93
00:12:05,705 --> 00:12:06,985
because I like men.

94
00:12:07,585 --> 00:12:09,865
I can never marry a woman
and give you grandkids.

95
00:12:09,944 --> 00:12:11,225
Calm down, Nut.

96
00:12:17,824 --> 00:12:18,985
Are you hurt

97
00:12:19,824 --> 00:12:21,184
to have me as a son?

98
00:12:23,585 --> 00:12:24,585
It hurts me, too,

99
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:26,665
that you're my mom.

100
00:12:31,944 --> 00:12:33,345
You can hate me all you want.

101
00:12:34,704 --> 00:12:37,225
But I will never be who you want me to be.

102
00:12:39,304 --> 00:12:40,225
Nut.

103
00:12:41,704 --> 00:12:43,064
If you want me to stay,

104
00:12:44,225 --> 00:12:45,265
I'll stay,

105
00:12:46,345 --> 00:12:47,985
but I'll be myself.

106
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:52,265
I'll love him like this.

107
00:12:58,145 --> 00:12:59,105
What are you doing?

108
00:13:09,265 --> 00:13:10,145
Nut.

109
00:13:20,145 --> 00:13:21,304
Nut.

110
00:13:30,704 --> 00:13:32,145
Nut.

111
00:13:32,225 --> 00:13:33,265
Nut.

112
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:34,544
Let's talk.

113
00:13:35,184 --> 00:13:38,105
You'll never understand
what I went through.

114
00:13:38,184 --> 00:13:39,824
All you do is side with her.

115
00:13:40,824 --> 00:13:42,064
I don't.

116
00:13:42,145 --> 00:13:43,704
I just didn't want you to do that.

117
00:13:44,585 --> 00:13:45,544
Nut.

118
00:13:46,544 --> 00:13:47,585
Nut!

119
00:14:06,905 --> 00:14:07,944
Song.

120
00:14:10,145 --> 00:14:10,985
Here.

121
00:14:16,625 --> 00:14:18,785
Why did you come all the way here?

122
00:14:20,905 --> 00:14:22,225
I had a fight with Tofu.

123
00:14:23,145 --> 00:14:24,385
I don't want to see him.

124
00:14:24,944 --> 00:14:26,064
What did he do?

125
00:14:28,745 --> 00:14:30,465
I'll change the question.

126
00:14:30,544 --> 00:14:33,225
What did you do?

127
00:14:37,665 --> 00:14:40,985
My mom knows I'm with Tofu.

128
00:14:42,704 --> 00:14:44,905
What did she say?

129
00:14:46,304 --> 00:14:47,824
I don't care

130
00:14:48,385 --> 00:14:49,665
if she yells at me.

131
00:14:50,745 --> 00:14:52,625
I won't break up with him like last time.

132
00:14:55,265 --> 00:14:57,345
Are you saying
that you broke up with your ex

133
00:14:57,865 --> 00:14:59,145
because of your mom?

134
00:15:08,785 --> 00:15:10,385
What does Tofu have to do with it?

135
00:15:13,064 --> 00:15:14,544
He doesn't understand me.

136
00:15:15,025 --> 00:15:18,385
I kissed him in front of Mom to spite her,

137
00:15:18,465 --> 00:15:20,665
and he just pushed me away.

138
00:15:23,345 --> 00:15:24,865
I wouldn't just push you away.

139
00:15:24,944 --> 00:15:27,025
I would dropkick you.

140
00:15:27,105 --> 00:15:29,465
Why are you acting like a child?

141
00:15:30,025 --> 00:15:33,544
Don't you ever consider his feelings?

142
00:15:34,625 --> 00:15:35,704
What about your mom's?

143
00:15:40,544 --> 00:15:41,385
Fine.

144
00:15:42,145 --> 00:15:43,265
I know I was wrong,

145
00:15:45,064 --> 00:15:46,385
but I wanted to hurt her

146
00:15:47,105 --> 00:15:48,225
like she hurt me before.

147
00:15:58,824 --> 00:15:59,944
All right.

148
00:16:01,745 --> 00:16:04,385
Hey, come. Let's have lunch.

149
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:07,025
Here. These are all Nut's favorites.

150
00:16:07,584 --> 00:16:08,584
It has been a while.

151
00:16:09,824 --> 00:16:10,665
Let's eat.

152
00:16:10,745 --> 00:16:12,025
He has a boyfriend now.

153
00:16:12,105 --> 00:16:13,985
He has forgotten about his friends.

154
00:16:15,505 --> 00:16:16,944
Stop talking about him.

155
00:16:18,304 --> 00:16:20,544
If I can't talk about him,
then you can leave.

156
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:21,824
Go home. Get out.

157
00:16:23,265 --> 00:16:25,985
Hey, you're always welcome here,

158
00:16:26,064 --> 00:16:29,704
but I would be glad
if you were happier at home.

159
00:16:40,944 --> 00:16:41,985
Who's here?

160
00:16:49,505 --> 00:16:51,785
How did you know Nut was here?

161
00:16:54,064 --> 00:16:56,985
Lovers should know each other well,

162
00:16:57,064 --> 00:16:58,505
just like how I know you.

163
00:17:00,424 --> 00:17:02,625
You brought Tofu all the way here,

164
00:17:03,184 --> 00:17:04,665
you can anticipate war.

165
00:17:16,704 --> 00:17:19,264
Our weekend seems jolly today.

166
00:17:24,704 --> 00:17:27,385
You guys must be hungry.

167
00:17:27,464 --> 00:17:29,385
Let's dig in.

168
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:30,504
-Come on.
-Okay.

169
00:17:30,585 --> 00:17:31,705
Let's eat.

170
00:17:40,305 --> 00:17:42,425
I remember that you like eggplant.

171
00:18:07,665 --> 00:18:09,665
-Nut.
-Get that for me.

172
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:14,465
I want that piece.

173
00:18:32,585 --> 00:18:34,465
-Nut.
-Give me some fried pork too.

174
00:18:51,465 --> 00:18:54,264
Do you want anything else?
I'll get it all for you now.

175
00:18:54,825 --> 00:18:55,744
I don't.

176
00:18:56,465 --> 00:18:57,905
Just eat. Don't bother me.

177
00:18:59,665 --> 00:19:02,625
How can I eat when you're mad?

178
00:19:04,425 --> 00:19:07,024
Whose fault is it that I'm mad?

179
00:19:07,105 --> 00:19:08,185
Hey.

180
00:19:08,264 --> 00:19:09,865
Whoever's fault it is,

181
00:19:09,945 --> 00:19:13,345
let's clear it up after we eat.

182
00:19:13,425 --> 00:19:15,625
It would be a shame to ruin lunch.

183
00:19:18,105 --> 00:19:21,465
I don't know what you fought about,

184
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:27,825
but there aren't many chances for us
to eat together like this.

185
00:19:28,385 --> 00:19:30,465
So the time that we spend together

186
00:19:30,945 --> 00:19:32,705
should be a happy time.

187
00:19:32,784 --> 00:19:35,825
The dining table is a war-free zone.

188
00:19:36,345 --> 00:19:38,065
-We should enjoy the food.
-Right.

189
00:19:40,905 --> 00:19:42,744
-I'm sorry.
-Okay.

190
00:19:42,825 --> 00:19:44,105
I'm sorry.

191
00:19:44,665 --> 00:19:46,425
All right. That's that.

192
00:19:46,504 --> 00:19:47,345
Let's eat,

193
00:19:47,425 --> 00:19:50,185
so we can cheer up with desserts.

194
00:20:02,305 --> 00:20:03,945
Do you think you own the place?

195
00:20:05,305 --> 00:20:06,665
What?

196
00:20:06,744 --> 00:20:09,705
You almost destroyed my home

197
00:20:09,784 --> 00:20:10,865
by bringing Tofu here.

198
00:20:10,945 --> 00:20:11,984
Just leave.

199
00:20:12,065 --> 00:20:13,024
I won't.

200
00:20:13,984 --> 00:20:15,984
-You won't?
-Right.

201
00:20:16,744 --> 00:20:18,504
Your dad invited me to stay.

202
00:20:27,945 --> 00:20:30,825
Nut. Talk it out nicely, okay?

203
00:20:36,345 --> 00:20:37,585
Thank you for lunch, Gen.

204
00:20:38,625 --> 00:20:40,185
Thank you, too, Song.

205
00:20:40,264 --> 00:20:41,545
Right.

206
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:43,665
Thank you for your meddling.

207
00:20:44,825 --> 00:20:46,145
I'm so darn touched.

208
00:20:46,905 --> 00:20:48,425
Let me tell you about Gen.

209
00:20:49,744 --> 00:20:52,065
-What are you doing, Nut?
-Don't worry.

210
00:21:03,305 --> 00:21:04,984
Nut. What did you say?

211
00:21:05,065 --> 00:21:06,185
You'll find out soon.

212
00:21:13,585 --> 00:21:15,744
What did he say, Song?

213
00:21:36,625 --> 00:21:37,465
What is this?

214
00:21:39,185 --> 00:21:40,345
Can we turn it off?

215
00:21:41,305 --> 00:21:43,385
Gosh, Nut.

216
00:21:45,305 --> 00:21:46,264
Nut.

217
00:21:48,385 --> 00:21:49,425
Ouch.

218
00:21:50,865 --> 00:21:51,945
Nut.

219
00:22:04,385 --> 00:22:05,465
Tofu.

220
00:22:28,905 --> 00:22:30,665
If something is bothering you,

221
00:22:32,544 --> 00:22:34,585
you can tell me.

222
00:22:36,065 --> 00:22:37,625
You might feel better.

223
00:22:47,465 --> 00:22:48,465
I'm sorry

224
00:22:50,024 --> 00:22:51,665
for what I did just now and at home.

225
00:22:54,425 --> 00:22:55,625
I'm not mad.

226
00:22:57,065 --> 00:23:00,264
I know you probably feel bad too.

227
00:23:01,825 --> 00:23:02,705
Don't you?

228
00:23:07,784 --> 00:23:08,984
I know I was wrong,

229
00:23:10,665 --> 00:23:12,585
but Mom was wrong too.

230
00:23:15,185 --> 00:23:16,625
It may be hard to imagine,

231
00:23:17,264 --> 00:23:18,744
but Mom and I used to be close.

232
00:23:20,465 --> 00:23:21,825
But as I grew up,

233
00:23:22,625 --> 00:23:23,625
I found out

234
00:23:24,385 --> 00:23:26,465
that we were never really close.

235
00:23:36,145 --> 00:23:37,784
-Mom.
-Yes?

236
00:23:37,865 --> 00:23:41,065
They say that Thailand
was never colonized.

237
00:23:41,145 --> 00:23:43,625
What about the two times we lost to Burma?

238
00:23:43,705 --> 00:23:45,065
Well…

239
00:23:45,905 --> 00:23:50,385
we only count the Western Colonization
during the Rattanakosin period,

240
00:23:51,024 --> 00:23:54,345
not during the Ayutthaya period,
since we weren't a country back then.

241
00:23:55,385 --> 00:23:58,105
What are the pros and cons

242
00:23:58,185 --> 00:24:00,425
of never being colonized?

243
00:24:04,385 --> 00:24:05,705
What are we talking about?

244
00:24:08,024 --> 00:24:09,225
I have something for you.

245
00:24:15,665 --> 00:24:16,945
I'm hungry.

246
00:24:17,825 --> 00:24:18,945
I'll cook you something.

247
00:24:49,185 --> 00:24:50,504
Isn't this pretty?

248
00:24:52,585 --> 00:24:56,345
Nut. That's a girl's dress.
You can't wear that.

249
00:25:00,065 --> 00:25:02,945
Why not? Can't boys wear it?

250
00:25:03,024 --> 00:25:04,705
I like this dress.

251
00:25:07,225 --> 00:25:09,865
Pink is for girls.

252
00:25:11,504 --> 00:25:13,865
What color is for boys, then?

253
00:25:13,945 --> 00:25:16,425
Why can't it be pink?

254
00:25:23,825 --> 00:25:26,264
Haven't I told you
not to let him play with these?

255
00:25:40,665 --> 00:25:41,665
Sib.

256
00:25:44,345 --> 00:25:46,665
-You shouldn't go so far--
-Shut it.

257
00:25:47,585 --> 00:25:50,225
He's turning gay
because of your negligence.

258
00:25:51,504 --> 00:25:53,984
-He's just a nice boy.
-Don't talk back to me.

259
00:25:54,465 --> 00:25:56,345
Boys have to be strong.

260
00:25:56,425 --> 00:25:58,585
What kind of mom are you?

261
00:27:10,304 --> 00:27:11,185
Nut!

262
00:27:13,784 --> 00:27:14,625
Honey!

263
00:27:15,825 --> 00:27:17,465
Hey! Stop!

264
00:27:18,425 --> 00:27:21,504
Do you see
he's wearing heels like a queen?

265
00:27:22,345 --> 00:27:24,145
Do you want to be one?

266
00:27:24,225 --> 00:27:25,865
Do you want to be gay?

267
00:27:25,945 --> 00:27:27,905
Don't you want to be a man?

268
00:27:28,744 --> 00:27:29,744
Answer me!

269
00:27:31,065 --> 00:27:32,185
What are you looking at?

270
00:27:43,264 --> 00:27:44,544
What did I do wrong?

271
00:27:45,544 --> 00:27:47,945
Why can't boys play with paper dolls?

