00:58:14,105 --> 00:58:15,665
I won't tell you any more stories.

554
00:58:15,745 --> 00:58:17,145
I'm really fine.

555
00:58:17,745 --> 00:58:18,785
Do you want a mirror?

556
00:58:19,265 --> 00:58:21,105
Your face doesn't look fine.

557
00:58:24,424 --> 00:58:27,424
I just envy him a little,

558
00:58:28,265 --> 00:58:29,665
I'm a bit jealous.

559
00:58:30,904 --> 00:58:32,745
But when it comes to your stories,

560
00:58:33,345 --> 00:58:34,585
I want to know everything.

561
00:58:36,665 --> 00:58:39,625
You're just thinking of him,

562
00:58:40,305 --> 00:58:41,785
but you aren't missing him.

563
00:58:47,345 --> 00:58:51,464
Finally, I got to know
how Nut ended up with Tatarn.

564
00:58:52,424 --> 00:58:54,864
Their love seemed fine,

565
00:58:55,984 --> 00:58:56,944
but…

566
00:58:57,745 --> 00:59:02,504
what happened
between Nut, Tatarn, and Nut's mom?

567
00:59:03,504 --> 00:59:06,625
Why have Nut and his mom
had a problem for so long?

568
00:59:11,265 --> 00:59:13,785
Right. What's your problem?

569
00:59:15,625 --> 00:59:17,904
My dad asked what the problem was.

570
00:59:17,984 --> 00:59:19,705
You've been watering for five minutes.

571
00:59:19,785 --> 00:59:21,625
My vegetables are probably dead.

572
00:59:22,665 --> 00:59:24,944
Gen cherishes that plot.

573
00:59:25,504 --> 00:59:27,305
It will rot if you water it too much.

574
00:59:27,384 --> 00:59:28,504
Gen will yell at you.

575
00:59:28,585 --> 00:59:30,464
I don't cherish it.

576
00:59:30,984 --> 00:59:32,585
My mistake.

577
00:59:33,065 --> 00:59:34,185
You used to cherish it.

578
00:59:34,984 --> 00:59:36,705
That plot was for his ex.

579
00:59:36,785 --> 00:59:38,065
Dad! Don't.

580
00:59:38,864 --> 00:59:39,864
Is that true?

581
00:59:43,904 --> 00:59:45,785
Yes. Well…

582
00:59:46,504 --> 00:59:48,265
my ex wouldn't eat vegetables,

583
00:59:48,345 --> 00:59:50,345
so I tried to get him to eat those.

584
00:59:51,585 --> 00:59:52,904
He would only eat those

585
00:59:52,984 --> 00:59:54,185
if I planted them.

586
00:59:56,384 --> 00:59:58,185
That kid liked cabbage,

587
00:59:58,265 --> 01:00:00,384
so he paid special attention to those.

588
01:00:00,464 --> 01:00:01,904
Dad! Again?

589
01:00:04,105 --> 01:00:06,305
I guess they're useless now
since you broke up.

590
01:00:07,024 --> 01:00:09,065
Can't I plant them for myself?

591
01:00:12,185 --> 01:00:13,665
I like ivy gourd leaves, though.

592
01:00:16,545 --> 01:00:17,464
Listen.

593
01:00:17,944 --> 01:00:19,305
When you leave my house,

594
01:00:19,384 --> 01:00:21,305
turn left and you'll find a market.

595
01:00:21,384 --> 01:00:23,904
Buy as many as you like.

596
01:00:25,904 --> 01:00:27,545
Come on, mister.

597
01:00:28,105 --> 01:00:29,864
I want you to plant those for me.

598
01:00:30,424 --> 01:00:31,345
Just like this.

599
01:00:31,825 --> 01:00:33,225
Please.

600
01:00:33,745 --> 01:00:35,705
-Just a few.
-Why should I?

601
01:00:38,864 --> 01:00:40,065
Plant them yourself.

602
01:00:41,464 --> 01:00:42,585
I have the seeds.

603
01:00:43,345 --> 01:00:45,665
Really? Where?

604
01:00:45,745 --> 01:00:46,904
Over there.

605
01:00:49,105 --> 01:00:50,305
I got them for free.

606
01:00:51,464 --> 01:00:53,785
Are my vegetables just a giveaway?

607
01:00:54,585 --> 01:00:56,825
Are you going to plant them or not?

608
01:00:59,585 --> 01:01:01,904
Of course, I am.

609
01:01:04,464 --> 01:01:05,384
Hey.

610
01:01:10,065 --> 01:01:11,984
Mr. Sitha, cool it.

611
01:01:12,065 --> 01:01:13,665
Well, yes.

612
01:01:13,745 --> 01:01:15,825
Yes. Okay.

613
01:02:20,904 --> 01:02:23,545
Wait. What's that?

614
01:02:23,625 --> 01:02:25,225
What's that?

615
01:02:26,904 --> 01:02:28,665
Meow.

616
01:02:30,145 --> 01:02:33,065
-Meow?
-Hey!

617
01:02:33,145 --> 01:02:35,464
What? Don't.

618
01:02:36,024 --> 01:02:37,904
I know why you like ivy gourd leaves.

619
01:02:37,984 --> 01:02:39,424
Why so?

620
01:02:39,944 --> 01:02:40,984
They're creepers.

621
01:02:41,065 --> 01:02:41,904
Hey.

622
01:02:41,984 --> 01:02:44,745
There. Take that.

623
01:02:44,825 --> 01:02:46,504
Come here, Song.

624
01:02:46,585 --> 01:02:47,944
Stop.

625
01:02:55,625 --> 01:02:56,864
I'll wash it for you.

626
01:02:57,864 --> 01:03:00,545
Come on. Stop pestering me.

627
01:03:00,625 --> 01:03:01,785
I'm tired of yelling.

628
01:03:06,145 --> 01:03:07,665
I'm not fooling around anymore.

629
01:03:09,864 --> 01:03:12,345
Let me ask something serious.

630
01:03:15,825 --> 01:03:17,265
Do you not like younger guys?

631
01:03:22,105 --> 01:03:23,504
What are you saying?

632
01:03:24,745 --> 01:03:27,585
Earlier, Nut told me…

633
01:03:28,665 --> 01:03:31,464
Gen won't like you.
He doesn't like younger guys.

634
01:03:32,984 --> 01:03:34,145
Is it because of your ex?

635
01:03:36,984 --> 01:03:37,984
Earlier,

636
01:03:38,065 --> 01:03:39,544
your father said you went out

637
01:03:39,625 --> 01:03:40,864
with someone younger.

638
01:03:45,705 --> 01:03:49,745
Did your ex-boyfriend traumatize you
from dating a younger man?

639
01:03:52,065 --> 01:03:54,745
Not all younger men are the same.

640
01:03:54,825 --> 01:03:56,065
Don't generalize us.

641
01:03:58,145 --> 01:04:00,384
The difference in our age
was only a few years,

642
01:04:00,904 --> 01:04:02,145
yet my ex and I broke up.

643
01:04:03,305 --> 01:04:05,384
Our age gap is nine years.

644
01:04:06,585 --> 01:04:08,705
What if you meet someone better
in the future?

645
01:04:09,984 --> 01:04:11,464
What if you become famous?

646
01:04:12,625 --> 01:04:14,225
Your life has a long way to go.

647
01:04:16,105 --> 01:04:18,665
That time hasn't come yet.

648
01:04:19,265 --> 01:04:20,544
Why would you worry?

649
01:04:24,904 --> 01:04:27,984
Do you think I'll turn out like them?

650
01:04:31,225 --> 01:04:33,065
Don't you have confidence in me

651
01:04:35,665 --> 01:04:37,904
when I'm with you at all?

652
01:04:46,424 --> 01:04:47,345
I…

653
01:04:49,745 --> 01:04:50,904
I don't want to risk it.

654
01:04:57,424 --> 01:04:58,864
Hey, Gen.

655
01:05:11,864 --> 01:05:13,065
Drink some water.

656
01:05:13,145 --> 01:05:14,105
Thank you.

657
01:05:18,345 --> 01:05:19,305
It's a little tough.

658
01:05:20,265 --> 01:05:21,944
Gen is a stubborn kid.

659
01:05:24,745 --> 01:05:27,544
I'm very serious about him.

660
01:05:29,024 --> 01:05:30,904
I don't know what else to do.

661
01:05:34,504 --> 01:05:37,024
Kanya and I were the same.

662
01:05:38,745 --> 01:05:40,625
When I pursued her,

663
01:05:40,705 --> 01:05:42,944
she was hard to get like Gen.

664
01:05:44,185 --> 01:05:48,504
When older women marry younger men,

665
01:05:48,585 --> 01:05:50,424
they worry about a million things.

666
01:05:51,424 --> 01:05:53,944
People would say
she's going out with her brother,

667
01:05:54,024 --> 01:05:56,185
or that she's my mom.

668
01:05:59,625 --> 01:06:01,625
What did you do, then?

669
01:06:02,544 --> 01:06:03,864
I just kept going?

670
01:06:05,225 --> 01:06:06,745
You just kept going?

671
01:06:08,424 --> 01:06:09,665
What else could I do?

672
01:06:11,065 --> 01:06:12,904
If you really like him,

673
01:06:12,984 --> 01:06:14,825
then show him that.

674
01:06:14,904 --> 01:06:15,745
Just do it.

675
01:06:16,904 --> 01:06:18,265
It won't be a waste.

676
01:06:20,825 --> 01:06:23,585
As Gen's father

677
01:06:24,065 --> 01:06:25,705
who raised him with my own hands,

678
01:06:26,665 --> 01:06:29,665
his life has always been a breeze.

679
01:06:30,225 --> 01:06:32,065
He got to study what he wanted.

680
01:06:32,864 --> 01:06:34,225
He has a good job.

681
01:06:34,944 --> 01:06:37,145
Nobody minds who he is.

682
01:06:37,225 --> 01:06:40,904
Kanya and I have always understood
and supported him,

683
01:06:42,024 --> 01:06:44,705
so he wants some things to be difficult.

684
01:06:46,305 --> 01:06:47,825
Love, for instance.

685
01:06:49,904 --> 01:06:52,145
I have to try harder, do I?

686
01:06:54,705 --> 01:06:56,225
Do your best, if you can.

687
01:06:57,464 --> 01:06:59,944
If you want some help, tell me.

688
01:07:01,864 --> 01:07:04,345
I'll understand if you want to give up.

689
01:07:05,024 --> 01:07:07,305
My son is high maintenance.

690
01:07:11,185 --> 01:07:12,384
Thank you.

691
01:07:18,625 --> 01:07:19,544
Cheer up.

692
01:07:28,864 --> 01:07:30,464
Have you two eaten?

693
01:07:48,305 --> 01:07:50,504
I'm sorry for keeping it from you.

694
01:07:52,145 --> 01:07:54,745
I didn't want to do that.

695
01:07:55,225 --> 01:07:57,984
I was just afraid you wouldn't like it,

696
01:07:59,625 --> 01:08:01,424
and that it would affect your health.

697
01:08:02,544 --> 01:08:05,145
I didn't want it to bother you.

698
01:08:10,785 --> 01:08:12,065
I'm sorry.

699
01:08:18,945 --> 01:08:20,305
What are you doing?

700
01:08:20,865 --> 01:08:22,225
I'm working.

701
01:08:23,584 --> 01:08:24,544
A change of scenery.

702
01:08:26,384 --> 01:08:28,704
I'm writing a boys' love screenplay.

703
01:08:29,384 --> 01:08:32,504
I get inspired with you around.

704
01:08:36,225 --> 01:08:39,865
I'll try not to make loud noises,
so you can focus on work.

705
01:08:42,664 --> 01:08:43,504
You want to know

706
01:08:44,865 --> 01:08:46,384
what I'm writing about?

707
01:08:49,905 --> 01:08:52,624
If you want to tell me, I'll listen.

708
01:08:54,265 --> 01:08:57,744
I'm writing about a boy's love.

709
01:08:59,544 --> 01:09:01,744
Despite being a high school love,

710
01:09:02,384 --> 01:09:04,384
it's not as jolly as a fantasy world.

711
01:09:05,265 --> 01:09:08,345
I won't write about
such an idealistic world.

712
01:09:10,185 --> 01:09:11,464
In reality,

713
01:09:12,185 --> 01:09:13,825
it's hard for men to be in love.

714
01:09:15,025 --> 01:09:17,305
Family, friends,

715
01:09:17,865 --> 01:09:19,865
or people next door don't accept it.

716
01:09:22,065 --> 01:09:23,464
That's just reality.

717
01:09:30,544 --> 01:09:33,744
Oh. It's time for Keunchai's dinner.

718
01:09:36,504 --> 01:09:38,504
He's probably starving.

719
01:09:38,584 --> 01:09:39,865
Then,

720
01:09:40,624 --> 01:09:42,225
I won't bother you anymore.

721
01:09:42,305 --> 01:09:43,704
Work hard.

722
01:09:45,544 --> 01:09:48,105
Come on, Keunchai. Let's eat.

723
01:09:48,185 --> 01:09:49,584
Come on.

724
01:09:50,825 --> 01:09:51,825
Let's eat.

725
01:10:01,624 --> 01:10:03,385
What are you trying to do?

726
01:10:06,624 --> 01:10:07,905
Aren't you curious to see

727
01:10:08,425 --> 01:10:09,945
what will happen if Mom sees us?

728
01:10:15,624 --> 01:10:16,744
Let me help.

729
01:10:19,145 --> 01:10:20,065
Tofu.

730
01:10:21,704 --> 01:10:22,825
I want coffee.

731
01:10:23,825 --> 01:10:25,465
Wait a second. I'm helping your mom.

732
01:10:26,145 --> 01:10:27,585
I want it now.

733
01:10:28,945 --> 01:10:30,945
You should make him coffee.

734
01:10:48,025 --> 01:10:49,385
You're so slow.

735
01:10:51,624 --> 01:10:52,784
Let me see it.

736
01:10:54,825 --> 01:10:56,065
What are you doing?

737
01:11:01,865 --> 01:11:04,225
I want your attention. Can't I do this?

738
01:11:10,105 --> 01:11:12,065
You usually know how to make coffee.

739
01:11:18,784 --> 01:11:20,225
Today, I forgot.

740
01:12:10,865 --> 01:12:12,065
In case you're hungry.

741
01:12:14,225 --> 01:12:15,385
Thank you,

742
01:12:16,465 --> 01:12:17,425
but I'm not.

743
01:12:23,505 --> 01:12:24,345
Tofu.

744
01:12:25,985 --> 01:12:28,385
Feed me. My hands are busy.

745
01:12:49,145 --> 01:12:49,985
Thanks.

746
01:13:10,385 --> 01:13:15,905
SCENE 36. BOOKSTORE. KAWEE, TONNAM.
KAWEE IS LOOKING AT BOOKS ON THE SHELF.

747
01:13:18,065 --> 01:13:24,385
KAWEE IS LOOKING
AT THE FRONT OF THE BOOKSTORE.

748
01:13:31,784 --> 01:13:33,545
I'll take it off for you.

749
01:13:36,825 --> 01:13:38,265
You can go.

750
01:13:49,225 --> 01:13:52,664
Since you're so inspired, any progress?

751
01:13:57,585 --> 01:13:58,624
Quite a lot.

752
01:13:59,585 --> 01:14:00,824
Perfect timing.

753
01:14:02,505 --> 01:14:03,465
Do a scene with me.

754
01:14:05,505 --> 01:14:06,624
What scene?

755
01:14:06,704 --> 01:14:07,744
You've only got that.

756
01:14:08,385 --> 01:14:10,624
Just do what I say.

757
01:14:11,185 --> 01:14:13,465
Stay still. I'll do the work.

758
01:14:15,744 --> 01:14:17,145
Let's do a romantic scene.

759
01:14:17,704 --> 01:14:19,545
Like this, Tofu.

760
01:14:20,225 --> 01:14:21,265
What are you doing?

761
01:14:21,345 --> 01:14:22,425
Come on.

762
01:14:23,704 --> 01:14:24,664
Nut.

763
01:14:28,624 --> 01:14:29,585
Nut!

764
01:14:33,664 --> 01:14:35,065
Let's talk.

765
01:14:41,865 --> 01:14:42,945
What's wrong with you?

766
01:14:44,985 --> 01:14:46,624
Why did you do that?

767
01:14:47,744 --> 01:14:50,345
You couldn't write a single scene anyway.

768
01:14:50,425 --> 01:14:52,145
That's my problem.

769
01:14:53,345 --> 01:14:56,505
It's not just your problem.
We live together.

770
01:15:00,025 --> 01:15:02,664
Are you saying that if you're not happy,

771
01:15:03,265 --> 01:15:05,305
no one else is allowed to be happy?

772
01:15:05,385 --> 01:15:06,345
That's not right.

773
01:15:06,425 --> 01:15:07,664
Tofu.

774
01:15:08,305 --> 01:15:09,225
You saw it.

775
01:15:09,744 --> 01:15:12,985
I went that far, but Mom still ignored me.

776
01:15:13,065 --> 01:15:15,945
The more she ignores me,
the more invisible I feel.

777
01:15:17,425 --> 01:15:20,664
Nut, it's not your fault
for being who you are,

778
01:15:21,225 --> 01:15:22,585
but it's not hers either.

779
01:15:23,545 --> 01:15:26,865
Your mom is just trying
to keep everyone in the household happy.

780
01:15:26,945 --> 01:15:28,345
It's fake happiness.

781
01:15:28,985 --> 01:15:30,545
She keeps fooling herself.

782
01:15:31,105 --> 01:15:32,784
She has never really known me.

783
01:15:33,305 --> 01:15:35,305
How can we love each other

784
01:15:36,145 --> 01:15:37,624
when we barely know each other?

785
01:15:38,664 --> 01:15:39,945
What do you want, then?

786
01:15:40,425 --> 01:15:43,905
If she knows the real you, she'll be hurt.

787
01:15:43,985 --> 01:15:46,945
When she's hurt, you're hurt.

788
01:15:47,425 --> 01:15:50,545
It's a circle of pain. When will it end?

789
01:15:53,105 --> 01:15:55,025
Why don't you try talking about it?

790
01:16:02,824 --> 01:16:05,465
I'm sorry.

791
01:16:05,545 --> 01:16:07,265
I didn't mean to eavesdrop.

792
01:16:07,345 --> 01:16:09,985
I just happened to hear it
while passing by.

793
01:16:10,065 --> 01:16:11,865
I'm really sorry.

794
01:16:12,585 --> 01:16:14,145
What are you fighting about?

795
01:16:23,025 --> 01:16:24,784
-I'm here.
-You're here.

796
01:16:24,865 --> 01:16:26,545
What took you so long?

797
01:16:26,624 --> 01:16:29,345
Gosh. Oh, take a seat.

798
01:16:30,545 --> 01:16:31,385
Well…

799
01:16:33,945 --> 01:16:35,265
Tofu.

800
01:16:35,345 --> 01:16:37,345
You don't look so good.

801
01:16:37,425 --> 01:16:38,824
Is there a problem at home?

802
01:16:40,505 --> 01:16:42,624
Nut and his mom are fighting.

803
01:16:43,824 --> 01:16:45,585
I don't know how to help.

804
01:16:46,585 --> 01:16:48,385
It's a tough job.

805
01:16:48,465 --> 01:16:50,105
Ever since I moved here,

806
01:16:50,185 --> 01:16:52,465
Na and Nut are always arguing.

807
01:16:52,545 --> 01:16:55,345
It's not that hard, Nhong.

808
01:16:55,945 --> 01:16:58,225
Of course, there's something we can do.

809
01:16:58,905 --> 01:16:59,824
Listen.

810
01:17:00,305 --> 01:17:04,185
Na and Nut are mother and son.

811
01:17:04,265 --> 01:17:07,225
Of course, they have some issues.
It's called a generation gap.

812
01:17:08,865 --> 01:17:10,465
Generation gap?

813
01:17:10,545 --> 01:17:11,465
Right.

814
01:17:12,025 --> 01:17:14,225
Nut grew up in an open world

815
01:17:14,305 --> 01:17:15,784
with freedom

816
01:17:15,865 --> 01:17:17,945
and all sorts of information.

817
01:17:18,505 --> 01:17:22,425
Whatever he does or asks, he needs facts.

818
01:17:22,505 --> 01:17:25,545
On the other hand,
Na is framed within her society.

819
01:17:25,624 --> 01:17:26,865
She's from my generation.

820
01:17:27,624 --> 01:17:29,985
She needs to be meticulous
in everything she does.

821
01:17:30,065 --> 01:17:31,784
That's her quality.

822
01:17:31,865 --> 01:17:34,145
She was taught that way
since she was born.

823
01:17:35,465 --> 01:17:37,985
They're from different generations.

824
01:17:38,065 --> 01:17:39,545
They both have expectations.

825
01:17:39,624 --> 01:17:41,784
Mother expects her son
to be a certain way.

826
01:17:41,865 --> 01:17:44,305
The son expects his mother
to be a certain way.

827
01:17:44,385 --> 01:17:47,744
The expectations
aren't met on either side,

828
01:17:47,824 --> 01:17:51,145
so they hurt each other
without realizing it.

829
01:17:56,425 --> 01:17:59,985
Wherever there's a gap,
you need to pay special attention.

830
01:18:00,065 --> 01:18:03,465
It can be dangerous
if the gap is too wide.

831
01:18:05,505 --> 01:18:07,305
How do we reduce the gap?

832
01:18:08,824 --> 01:18:09,664
Hey.

833
01:18:09,744 --> 01:18:12,025
The gap can be filled

834
01:18:12,105 --> 01:18:13,624
with family ties.

835
01:18:13,704 --> 01:18:16,105
If Nut and Na love each other,

836
01:18:16,185 --> 01:18:17,744
they should talk it out

837
01:18:17,824 --> 01:18:19,265
and maintain the ties.

838
01:18:19,345 --> 01:18:21,824
It will be fine
as long as they communicate.

839
01:18:27,545 --> 01:18:29,824
Because Mrs. Na and Nut won't communicate.

840
01:18:30,945 --> 01:18:34,385
she does things
without asking what Nut wants,

841
01:18:34,465 --> 01:18:36,624
as she thinks those are her duties

842
01:18:37,185 --> 01:18:38,225
as a mother.

843
01:18:40,065 --> 01:18:42,065
Nut also has demands from his mom.

844
01:18:42,585 --> 01:18:44,065
He always acts sarcastically,

845
01:18:44,664 --> 01:18:46,905
but he doesn't tell her what he wants.

846
01:18:50,305 --> 01:18:53,065
The gap between mother and child
should be narrow,

847
01:18:53,744 --> 01:18:55,425
but it keeps widening.

848
01:18:56,945 --> 01:18:58,624
I don't want it to be like this.

849
01:18:59,985 --> 01:19:01,545
Is there a way I can help them?

850
01:19:22,664 --> 01:19:23,664
I'm sorry.

851
01:19:28,025 --> 01:19:28,945
Okay.

852
01:19:31,225 --> 01:19:33,145
It's not all your fault.

853
01:19:34,425 --> 01:19:36,784
I don't know how hard it is to be you,

854
01:19:38,185 --> 01:19:40,624
but it's not easy being your mom either.

855
01:19:43,585 --> 01:19:45,905
You might have faced
many things in your life,

856
01:19:48,065 --> 01:19:49,545
but your mom has too.

857
01:19:52,865 --> 01:19:55,265
I want you to think about her feelings.

858
01:20:00,265 --> 01:20:01,744
Thanks for reminding me.

859
01:20:03,145 --> 01:20:04,985
I'll try to be a better person.

860
01:20:07,985 --> 01:20:10,425
You're not that bad.

861
01:20:11,664 --> 01:20:13,265
Try to be positive.

862
01:20:14,985 --> 01:20:18,425
I think there are a lot more good things
in your life.

863
01:20:20,385 --> 01:20:23,505
You're the good thing in my life.

864
01:20:26,545 --> 01:20:27,784
It's not just me.

865
01:20:29,065 --> 01:20:30,664
Think harder.

866
01:20:35,225 --> 01:20:36,624
I told you.

867
01:20:37,265 --> 01:20:38,824
I won't talk about him anymore.

868
01:20:40,945 --> 01:20:42,225
It's okay.

869
01:20:42,945 --> 01:20:45,025
I want to know everything about you.

870
01:20:47,465 --> 01:20:49,505
I don't want you to act fine,

871
01:20:50,425 --> 01:20:52,185
when you're actually not.

872
01:20:56,744 --> 01:20:59,065
As long as you're not hurt
when you talk about it,

873
01:21:00,905 --> 01:21:02,305
I'll be fine.

874
01:21:09,065 --> 01:21:10,185
Continue.

875
01:21:11,624 --> 01:21:14,465
After you agreed to go out with Tatarn,

876
01:21:15,345 --> 01:21:16,905
how happy were you?

877
01:21:19,065 --> 01:21:20,704
It wasn't just happiness.

878
01:21:25,465 --> 01:21:26,664
The world at home

879
01:21:28,185 --> 01:21:30,065
and the world when I was with him

880
01:21:31,065 --> 01:21:32,305
were drastically different.

881
01:21:48,945 --> 01:21:49,824
Nut.

882
01:21:50,425 --> 01:21:53,145
Don't spend too much time on activities.

883
01:21:53,824 --> 01:21:55,664
Your dad is worried about your grades.

884
01:21:59,704 --> 01:22:01,185
And regarding that other matter,

885
01:22:01,265 --> 01:22:02,345
you should behave.

886
01:22:03,664 --> 01:22:06,824
I won't stand it if you disobey me.

887
01:22:10,145 --> 01:22:11,345
Let's eat.

888
01:22:11,425 --> 01:22:12,545
I already ate.

889
01:22:25,305 --> 01:22:28,945
My parents act like I don't fit in

890
01:22:29,025 --> 01:22:31,865
and that it's embarrassing.

891
01:22:45,225 --> 01:22:46,185
Hey, Nut.

892
01:22:51,704 --> 01:22:52,945
I wrote it.

893
01:23:07,744 --> 01:23:08,664
How is it?

894
01:23:10,624 --> 01:23:11,865
It's great.

895
01:23:15,425 --> 01:23:17,065
-Really?
-Yes.

896
01:23:23,385 --> 01:23:25,664
You could become a writer.

897
01:23:28,425 --> 01:23:29,585
But Tarn

898
01:23:30,985 --> 01:23:33,744
made me feel like
I had discovered another world.

899
01:23:35,664 --> 01:23:36,945
He made me feel like

900
01:23:38,225 --> 01:23:40,385
I wasn't the only odd one out anymore.

901
01:25:46,664 --> 01:25:48,624
Having a rough guy like him around,

902
01:25:49,664 --> 01:25:52,505
who dared to do things
that wouldn't hurt anyone,

903
01:25:53,065 --> 01:25:56,345
got me to open my mind
and I started to feel free.

904
01:26:18,145 --> 01:26:19,105
Wait.

905
01:26:21,704 --> 01:26:22,784
Nut!

906
01:26:32,465 --> 01:26:33,744
Happy birthday, Nut.

907
01:26:36,225 --> 01:26:38,105
I didn't think I would get one this year.

908
01:26:39,305 --> 01:26:40,784
I wouldn't forget your birthday.

909
01:26:40,865 --> 01:26:43,105
I added jelly for you since you like it.

910
01:26:47,425 --> 01:26:48,585
Thank you.

911
01:26:49,664 --> 01:26:50,505
Try it.

912
01:27:03,385 --> 01:27:04,225
Is it good?

913
01:27:06,025 --> 01:27:07,065
Feed me.

914
01:27:09,185 --> 01:27:11,824
Okay. You can have a big bite.

915
01:27:11,905 --> 01:27:12,945
Is it too big?

916
01:27:14,065 --> 01:27:14,945
Is it too big?

917
01:27:16,704 --> 01:27:18,065
Here you go.

918
01:27:19,025 --> 01:27:20,145
Oh, wow.

919
01:28:17,065 --> 01:28:18,145
Your lips are sweet

920
01:28:19,505 --> 01:28:20,784
and soft like jelly.

921
01:28:38,065 --> 01:28:42,145
What happened to you in the past
made you lose faith in love,

922
01:28:42,225 --> 01:28:43,305
NEXT EPISODE

923
01:28:43,385 --> 01:28:46,784
but I'm going to show you
how serious I am about you.

924
01:28:46,864 --> 01:28:49,824
The reason you blow up at your mom…

925
01:28:52,945 --> 01:28:55,545
is to resist the feeling of love.

926
01:28:56,505 --> 01:28:58,744
But now that you've acknowledged
what happened,

927
01:29:00,185 --> 01:29:02,864
you feel better, don't you?

928
01:29:04,624 --> 01:29:06,265
You get irritable with your mom,

929
01:29:07,105 --> 01:29:08,664
but you're not really angry.

930
01:29:09,345 --> 01:29:11,465
You just…

931
01:29:12,465 --> 01:29:13,704
hold a grudge.

932
01:29:14,265 --> 01:29:15,624
You're such a know-it-all.

933
01:29:16,905 --> 01:29:18,265
Mom.

934
01:29:18,345 --> 01:29:20,025
-Mom!
-Mrs. Na.

